{"id": "1503198817955352617", "channel_id": "1503198817955352617", "type": 0, "author_id": "195179528241414145", "author_name": "phainos", "author_bot": false, "content": "I'm a new player (slightly more than a week) without many of the awakeners. I discovered that when using Tawil's exalt in the aequor realm to discover Voltice's card \"Reload!\" and using it, it does not apply the Vortex reload buff without Voltice being in the team. Am I doing something wrongly? or does the \"Vortex Shell\" pursuit require Voltice to proc? \n\nA friend of mine tried testing this interaction with his tawil and voltice and realises that it functions properly with voltice in the team. And even used a \"Reload!\" that was copied by Tawil's \"Omniscient Verity\" card and does see the vortex reload icon being shown under his buff bar.", "timestamp": "2026-05-11T00:55:26.284000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1503198817955352617", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tawil - Voltice Unintended interaction (?)", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"], "is_thread_starter": true}
